                                                                                                                                                  All the formulas of the course

                                                                                                                                                  Learning process

                                                                                                                                                  Error function

                                                                                                                                                  • Pointwise loss l(f,z)
                                                                                                                                                  E(f,pdata) = 𝔼z∼pdata[l(f,z)]E(f,Dn) = 1n∑i=1nl(f,zi)

                                                                                                                                                  Notation (Expected value)

                                                                                                                                                  𝔼[X]=μ=∑ixiP(xi)

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Regularization

                                                                                                                                                  Regularization: modification of the training error function with a term Ω(f) that penalizes complex solutions

                                                                                                                                                  Ereg(f,Dn)=E(f,Dn)+λnΩ(f)
                                                                                                                                                  • Ω(f): regularization term
                                                                                                                                                  • λn: trade-off hyper parameter

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Objectives

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Distance measures

                                                                                                                                                  Minkowski distance

                                                                                                                                                  Generalization of Euclidean distance

                                                                                                                                                  D(a,b)=(∑k=1p|ak−bk|r)1/r

                                                                                                                                                  • p : dimensions

                                                                                                                                                  • r : parameter (could be a hyper-parameter)

                                                                                                                                                    • r=1: Manhattan (L1-norm, city block, taxi)

                                                                                                                                                    • r=2: Euclidean (L2-norm)

                                                                                                                                                    • r→∞: supremum (L∞-norm) distance

                                                                                                                                                      • Maximum difference between any component of the vectors

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Cosine similarity

                                                                                                                                                  SC(a,b)=cos⁡(θ)=a·b‖a‖·‖b‖=∑k=1pak·bk∑k=1pak2·∑k=1pbk2D(a,b)=1−SC(a,b)
                                                                                                                                                  • ‖a‖: length of vector a

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Standardization & Scaling

                                                                                                                                                  Make not comparable features equally important

                                                                                                                                                  Formula (Standardization / Z-score normalization)

                                                                                                                                                  Rescale the data so that the mean (μ) is 0 and the standard deviation from the mean (standard score σ) is 1

                                                                                                                                                  xnorm=x−μσ

                                                                                                                                                  Formula (Min-Max scaling)

                                                                                                                                                  Scale the data to a fixed range between 0 and 1

                                                                                                                                                  xnorm=x−xminxmax−xmin

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Linear model

                                                                                                                                                  Hyperplane

                                                                                                                                                  wTx+b=∑i=1nwifi+b=0
                                                                                                                                                  • n : dimensions
                                                                                                                                                  • w: weight vector of n weights wi
                                                                                                                                                  • b : bias parameter

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Perceptron update

                                                                                                                                                  loop until convergence or for some_number_of_iterations:
                                                                                                                                                      foreach training_example {[f1, f2, ..., fn], label}:
                                                                                                                                                          prediction = b + Σ wj * fj   /* check if it is correct based on the current model  */
                                                                                                                                                          if prediction * label <= 0:  /* if prediction is incorrect, update all the weights */
                                                                                                                                                              foreach wj: wj += fj * label
                                                                                                                                                              b += label

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Loss functions

                                                                                                                                                  Notation

                                                                                                                                                  Notations

                                                                                                                                                  • Indicator function: turns True and False answers into numbers/counts

                                                                                                                                                    1[x]={1x=True0x=False

                                                                                                                                                  • Vector notation: represents an example f1,f2,…,fm as a single vector x

                                                                                                                                                    • xi subscript will indicate examples indexing over a dataset
                                                                                                                                                    • xj subscript will indicate feature indexing

                                                                                                                                                  • Vector dot-product: between two vectors a and b

                                                                                                                                                    a·b=∑j=1majbj

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Surrogate loss functions

                                                                                                                                                  Surrogate loss function: loss function that provides an upper bound on the actual loss function

                                                                                                                                                  • 0/1 loss:  l(y,y′)=1[yy′≤0]

                                                                                                                                                  • Hinge: l(y,y′)=max(0,1−yy′)

                                                                                                                                                    • SVM

                                                                                                                                                  • Exponential:   l(y,y′)=exp⁡(−yy′)

                                                                                                                                                  • Squared loss: l(y,y′)=(y−y′)2

                                                                                                                                                    • Regression, classification

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Linear model definition

                                                                                                                                                  1. Model

                                                                                                                                                    0=b+∑i=1nwifi

                                                                                                                                                  2. Objective function

                                                                                                                                                    ∑loss(yy′)+λr(w,b)

                                                                                                                                                  3. Learning algorithm

                                                                                                                                                    argminw,b∑loss(yy′)+λr(w,b)
                                                                                                                                                    • Find w and b that minimize the (surrogate) loss

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Gradient descent

                                                                                                                                                  Finding the minimum

                                                                                                                                                  Procedure (Gradient descent)

                                                                                                                                                  1. Pick a starting point w

                                                                                                                                                  2. Repeat until loss doesn’t decrease in any dimension

                                                                                                                                                    1. Pick a dimension
                                                                                                                                                    2. Move a small amount in that dimension towards decreasing loss
                                                                                                                                                    3. Update the parameters according to the graph
                                                                                                                                                    wj −=ηddwjloss(w)
                                                                                                                                                  • Partial derivatives gives the slope (i.e. direction to move) in that dimension

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Maths

                                                                                                                                                  ddwjloss(w) =ddwj∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi(w⋅xi+b))=∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi(w⋅xi+b))ddwj−yi(w⋅xi+b)−ddwjyi(w⋅xi+b) =−ddwjyi(∑j=1mwjxij+b)=−ddwjyi(w1xi1+w2xi2+…+wmxim+b)=−ddwjyi(w1xi1+yiw2xi2+…+yiwmxim+yib)=−yixijddwjloss(w) =ddwj∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi(w⋅xi+b))=∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi(w⋅xi+b))ddwj−yi(w⋅xi+b)=∑i=1n−yixijexp⁡(−yi(w⋅xi+b))

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Exponential update

                                                                                                                                                  • Gradient descent
                                                                                                                                                  wj −=ηddwjloss(w)⇒wj +=η∑i=1nyixijexp⁡(−yi(w·xi+b))
                                                                                                                                                  • Stochastic gradient descent: for each example xi (randomly selected)
                                                                                                                                                  wj += η  yixij ⏟directionto update exp⁡(−yi(w·xi+b)) ⏟how farfrom wrongc=ηexp⁡(−yi(w·xi+b))⇒wj+=yixijc

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Gradient

                                                                                                                                                  Gradient: vector of partial derivatives of the loss w.r.t. to all the coordinates of the weights

                                                                                                                                                  ∇wL=[∂L∂w1 ∂L∂w2⋯∂L∂wN]

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Regularizers

                                                                                                                                                  Regularization

                                                                                                                                                  Definition (Regularizer)

                                                                                                                                                  Additional criterion to the loss function to avoid overfitting

                                                                                                                                                  argminw,b⁡∑i=1nloss⁡(yy′)+λr(w,b)

                                                                                                                                                  Bias on the model that forces the learning to prefer certain types of weights over others

                                                                                                                                                  Definition (Regularization)

                                                                                                                                                  Modification of the training error function with a term Ω(f) that penalizes complex solutions

                                                                                                                                                  Ereg(f,Dn)=E(f,Dn)+λnΩ(f)
                                                                                                                                                  • Ω(f): regularization term
                                                                                                                                                  • λn: trade-off hyper parameter

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Common regularizers

                                                                                                                                                  argminw,b⁡∑i=1nloss⁡(yy′)+λ r(w,b)

                                                                                                                                                  • L1-norm: r(w,b)=∑|wj|

                                                                                                                                                    • Sum of weights penalize small values more

                                                                                                                                                  • L2-norm: r(w,b)=∑|wj|2

                                                                                                                                                    • Squared weights penalizes large values more

                                                                                                                                                  • Lp-norm: r(w,b)=∑|wj|pp=‖w‖p

                                                                                                                                                    • p≥1 leads to convex functions
                                                                                                                                                    • p<2 encourage sparser vectors (lots of 0 weights)
                                                                                                                                                    • p>2 discourage large weights more and tends to like similar weights

                                                                                                                                                  Notation (p-norm)

                                                                                                                                                  ‖x‖p := ∑|x|pp

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Exponential loss + L2-norm

                                                                                                                                                  1. Model

                                                                                                                                                    0=b+∑i=1nwifi

                                                                                                                                                  2. Objective function

                                                                                                                                                    ∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))+λ2‖w‖2

                                                                                                                                                  3. Learning algorithm

                                                                                                                                                    argminw,b∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))+λ2‖w‖2

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  GD Maths

                                                                                                                                                  wj −=ηddwj(loss(w)+λr(w,b))
                                                                                                                                                  ddwjobjective(w,b)=ddwj(loss(w)+λr(w,b))=ddwj∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))+λ2‖w‖2…=−∑i=1nyixijexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))+λwj

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  L2 update

                                                                                                                                                  wj −=ηddwj(loss(w)+λr(w,b))

                                                                                                                                                  • Gradient Descent

                                                                                                                                                    wj +=η∑i=1nyixijexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))−ηλwj

                                                                                                                                                  • Stochastic Gradient Descent

                                                                                                                                                    wj +=η  yixij ⏟directionto update   exp⁡(−yi(w·xi+b)) ⏟how farfrom wrong −ηλwj⏟regularization

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  L1 update

                                                                                                                                                  argminw,b∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))+λ‖w‖ddwj∑i=1nexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))+λ‖w‖=−∑i=1nyixijexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))+λsign(wj)wj +=ηyixijexp⁡(−yi·(w·xi+b))−ηλsign(wj)

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  p-norm update

                                                                                                                                                  • L1: wj +=η(lossCorrection−λsign(wj))
                                                                                                                                                  • L2: wj +=η(lossCorrection−λwj)
                                                                                                                                                  • Lp: wj +=η(lossCorrection−λcwjp−1)

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Support Vectors Machines

                                                                                                                                                  Measuring the margin

                                                                                                                                                  Margin: distance to the support vectors on either side of the hyperplane that corresponds to 1‖w‖

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Maximizing the margin

                                                                                                                                                  maxw,b margin(w,b) ≡ maxw,b1‖w‖ ≡ minw,b‖w‖subject to:   yi(w·xi+b)≥1   ∀i
                                                                                                                                                  • Constrained optimization problem

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Primal SVM problem

                                                                                                                                                  minw,b‖w‖2s.t.   yi(w·xi+b)≥1   ∀i
                                                                                                                                                  • Quadratic optimization problem

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Soft margin classification

                                                                                                                                                  Slack variables

                                                                                                                                                  minw,b‖w‖2+C∑iςis.t.   yi(w·xi+b)≥1−ςi ∧ ςi≥0   ∀i
                                                                                                                                                  • Quadratic optimization problem

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Slack values

                                                                                                                                                  yi(w·xi+b)≥1−ςi∧ςi≥0∀i
                                                                                                                                                  ςi={0 yi(w·xi+b)≥11−yi(w·xi+b) otherwiseςi=max(0,1−yi(w·xi+b))=max(0,1−yy′)=losshinge(y,y′) 

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Removing constraints

                                                                                                                                                  minw,b‖w‖2+C∑iςis.t.   yi(w·xi+b)≥1−ςi ∧ ςi≥0   ∀iminw,b‖w‖2+C∑imax(0,1−yi(w·xi+b))==minw,b‖w‖2+C∑ilosshinge(y,y′)
                                                                                                                                                  • Unconstrained problem

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Non linearly separable data

                                                                                                                                                  Dual problem

                                                                                                                                                  maxα∑iαi−12∑i∑jαiαjyiyjxiTxjs.t.   ∑iαiyi=0, αi≥0, ∀i

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Soft margin

                                                                                                                                                  maxα∑iαi−12∑i∑jαiαjyiyjxiTxjs.t.   ∑iαiyi=0, 0≤αi≤C, ∀i

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Solution

                                                                                                                                                  • Solution to the primal (given a solution α1…αn to the dual problem)

                                                                                                                                                    w=∑iαiyixi b=yj−∑iαiyixiTxj

                                                                                                                                                  • Classifying function

                                                                                                                                                    f(xj)=wTxj+b=∑iαiyixiTxj+b

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Kernel trick

                                                                                                                                                  K(xi,xj)=xiTxj⇒K′(xi,xj)=φ(xi)Tφ(xj)

                                                                                                                                                  Example (Polinomial kernel)

                                                                                                                                                  • Data

                                                                                                                                                    • 2-dimensional vectors x=[x1, x2]

                                                                                                                                                    • Let K(xi,xj)=(1+xiTxj)2

                                                                                                                                                      • Polinomial kernel

                                                                                                                                                  • Task: show that K(xi,xj)=φ(xi)Tφ(xj)

                                                                                                                                                  K(xi,xj)=(1+xiTxj)2=1+xi12xj12+2xi1xj1xi2xj2+xi22xj22+2xi1xj1+2xi2xj2==[1xi12√2xi1xi2xi22√2xi1√2xi2]T[1xj12√2xj1xj2xj22√2xj1√2xj2]==φ(xi)Tφ(xj),   where  φ(x)=[1, x12, √2x1x2, x22, √2x1, √2x2]

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Types of kernels

                                                                                                                                                  • Linear K(xi,xj)=xiTxj

                                                                                                                                                  • Polynomial of power p K(xi,xj)=(1+xiTxj)p

                                                                                                                                                  • Gaussian (radial-basis function) K(xi,xj)=e−‖xi−xj‖22σ2

                                                                                                                                                    • Mapping Φ:x→φ(x), where φ(x) is infinite-dimensional

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Non linear SVM problem

                                                                                                                                                  • Dual problem formulation

                                                                                                                                                    maxα∑iαi−12∑i∑jαiαjyiyjK(xi,xj)s.t.   ∑iαiyi=0, αi≥0, ∀i

                                                                                                                                                  • Solution

                                                                                                                                                    f(x)=∑iαiyiK(xi,x)+b

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Ranking

                                                                                                                                                  ω-ranking

                                                                                                                                                  Task (ω-ranking)

                                                                                                                                                  • Given

                                                                                                                                                    • Input space X
                                                                                                                                                    • Unknown distribution D over X×ΣM
                                                                                                                                                    • Training set D sampled from D

                                                                                                                                                  • Compute

                                                                                                                                                    • Function f:X→ΣM minimizing

                                                                                                                                                      E(x,σ)∼D[∑u≠v[σu<σv][σ^v<σ^u] ω(σu,σv)]
                                                                                                                                                      • Where σ^=f(x)

                                                                                                                                                  • Loss

                                                                                                                                                    • If the true ranking σ prefers u to v, but the predicted ranking σ^ prefers v to u, then the cost is ω(σu,σv)

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Decision Trees

                                                                                                                                                  Learning algorithm

                                                                                                                                                  • Given: training set Dn={z1,…,zn}

                                                                                                                                                  • Objective: find ft∗, where

                                                                                                                                                    t∗∈argmint∈TE(ft,Dn)
                                                                                                                                                    • T: set of decision trees

                                                                                                                                                  • Assumption

                                                                                                                                                    E(ft,D)=1|D|∑z∈Dl(f,z)

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Growing a leaf

                                                                                                                                                  Optimal leaf predictor: function that minimizes the error on a set

                                                                                                                                                  Definition (Imputity I(D) of a set D w.r.t. label y′)

                                                                                                                                                  • Given a set of examples D and a label y′ to test

                                                                                                                                                  • Value: the percentage of examples (x,y)∈D that aren’t labeled with y′

                                                                                                                                                    I(D)=|{(x,y)∈D:y≠y′}||D|

                                                                                                                                                  • Optimal leaf predictor

                                                                                                                                                    h∗∈argminh∈HleafE(h,D)

                                                                                                                                                  • Optimal error value (impurity measure)

                                                                                                                                                    I(D)=E(hD∗,D)

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Growing a node

                                                                                                                                                  Definition (Impurity Iϕ(D) of a split function ϕ)

                                                                                                                                                  Lowest training error attainable by a tree consisting of a root and two leaves, computed in terms of the impurity of the split data

                                                                                                                                                  Iϕ(D)=∑d∈{L,R}|Ddϕ||D| I(Ddϕ)

                                                                                                                                                  • Find an optimal split function

                                                                                                                                                    ϕD∗∈argminϕ∈ΦIϕ(D)

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Growing in a nutshell

                                                                                                                                                  Grow(D)={Leaf(hD∗) if stopping criterion met Node(ϕD∗, Grow(DL∗), Grow(DR∗)) otherwise whereDd∗={(x,y)∈D, ϕD∗(x)=d}

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Split selection

                                                                                                                                                  • Reduction of impurity, equivalent to information gain, induced by the split
                                                                                                                                                  Δϕ(D)=I(D)−Iϕ(D)

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Impurity measures for classification

                                                                                                                                                  • Let: Dy={(x,y′)∈D:y′=y} denotes the subset of training samples in D with class label y

                                                                                                                                                  • Consider: error function

                                                                                                                                                    E(f,D)=1|D|∑z∈Dl(f,z)

                                                                                                                                                  • Impurity measure defined as classification error

                                                                                                                                                    l(f,(x,y))=loss01(f,z) ∧ Hleaf=⋃y∈Y{y}X⇒I(D)=1−maxy∈Y|Dy||D|

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Neural Networks

                                                                                                                                                  Feed-forward Neural Networks

                                                                                                                                                  Perceptron

                                                                                                                                                  y^=h(∑iwixi+w0)=h(wTx+w0)

                                                                                                                                                  Simplified model

                                                                                                                                                  z=∑iwixi+w0

                                                                                                                                                  Multiple outputs

                                                                                                                                                  zj=∑iwi,jxi+w0,j

                                                                                                                                                  Single layer neural network

                                                                                                                                                  zj=∑iwi,j(1)xi+w0,j(1)y^k=f(∑iwi,k(2) h(zi)+w0,k(2))

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Softmax

                                                                                                                                                  • Convert outputs into normalized probabilities

                                                                                                                                                    S(li)=eli∑kelk
                                                                                                                                                    • li: scores (logits)
                                                                                                                                                    • k : number of classes

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Cross entropy loss

                                                                                                                                                  Li=−∑kyklog⁡(S(lk))=−log⁡(S(l))

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Backpropagation update

                                                                                                                                                  • First layer

                                                                                                                                                    wij(1) −= η∂L∂wij(1) = ηδjzi

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Step 1: Feedforward operation

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Step 2: Compute error and train (output layer)

                                                                                                                                                  • Error of the network on a training set

                                                                                                                                                    L(x,w)=12∑i=1N(yi−y^(xi,w))2

                                                                                                                                                  • Simple linear model for output y^i=∑jwjxij

                                                                                                                                                    ∂L(xi)∂wj=(y^i−yi)⏟error  xij

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Step 3: Backpropagation (hidden layers)

                                                                                                                                                  • General unit activation in a multilayer network

                                                                                                                                                  • Forward propagation: calculate for each unit at=∑jwjtzj

                                                                                                                                                    ∂L∂wjt=∂L∂at∂at∂wjt=∂L∂at⏟δtzj=δtzj

                                                                                                                                                  • Value: local gradient δt

                                                                                                                                                    • Output units with linear activation

                                                                                                                                                      δt=y^−y

                                                                                                                                                    • Hidden units

                                                                                                                                                      • Unit t sends output to units S
                                                                                                                                                      • δt is computed recursively using δs of the following layer
                                                                                                                                                      δt =∑s∈S∂L∂as∂as∂at = h′(at)∑s∈Swtsδsas=∑j:j→swjsh(aj)

                                                                                                                                                  Dimensionality reduction

                                                                                                                                                  Variance along unit direction w

                                                                                                                                                  • Given (in an n-dimensional space)

                                                                                                                                                    • Training set containing points xi
                                                                                                                                                    • Auxiliary point c
                                                                                                                                                    • Unit direction: vector w starting in c s.t. wTw=1

                                                                                                                                                  • Let

                                                                                                                                                    • Projection ti of vector xi−c on vector w

                                                                                                                                                      ti=(xi−c)Tw

                                                                                                                                                    • Set t of projections

                                                                                                                                                      t={ti : ti=(xi−c)Tw, ∀xi∈D}

                                                                                                                                                    • Vector X¯ of distances from mean x¯i=xi−x¯

                                                                                                                                                      X¯=[x¯1, x¯1, ..., x¯n]
                                                                                                                                                      • Centering data points

                                                                                                                                                  • Calculate: expectation (mean) and variance of set of vectors t

                                                                                                                                                    E[t] = 1n∑i=1nti= 1n∑i=1n(xi−c)Tw= x¯Tw−cTw Var[t] = 1n∑i=1n(ti−E[t])2== 1n∑i=1n((xi−x¯)Tw)2== 1n∑i=1n(x¯iTw)2== wT[1nX¯X¯T]w== wTCw
                                                                                                                                                    • Where: C=[1nX¯X¯T] is the covariance matrix
                                                                                                                                                    • Note: variance do not use c

                                                                                                                                                  • Objective: find vector w that maximize the variance

                                                                                                                                                    w∈arg⁡max{wTCw : wTw=1}

                                                                                                                                                  Eigenvalue Decomposition

                                                                                                                                                  Procedure (Eigenvalue Decomposition)

                                                                                                                                                  • Given: symmetric matrix A∈ℝm×m

                                                                                                                                                  • Objective: decompose A in UΛUT, so that it’s written in terms of its eigs

                                                                                                                                                    ∃U=[u1,...,um]∈ℝm×m,  Λ=(λ1,...,λm)∈ℝm:λ1≥⋯≥λms.t.A=UΛUT=∑j=1mλjujujT  ∧  UTU=UUT=I

                                                                                                                                                  • Where

                                                                                                                                                    • I: identity matrix
                                                                                                                                                    • uj: eigenvector
                                                                                                                                                    • λj: corresponding eigenvalue
                                                                                                                                                    • U: matrix containing eigenvectors in columns
                                                                                                                                                    • Λ: diagonal matrix of eigenvalues
                                                                                                                                                    U=[u1⋯un]Λ=[λ1⋯0⋮⋱⋮0⋯λn]

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Principal Components

                                                                                                                                                  • First Principal Component
                                                                                                                                                  w1∈arg⁡max{wTCw⏟variance along w : wTw=1}
                                                                                                                                                  • Second Principal Component
                                                                                                                                                  w2∈arg⁡max{wTCw : wTw=1, w⊥w1}
                                                                                                                                                  • i-th Principal Component
                                                                                                                                                  wi∈arg⁡max{wTCw : wTw=1, w⊥wj, ∀ 1≤j<i}

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Singular Value Decomposition (SVD)

                                                                                                                                                  Procedure (Singular Value Decomposition)

                                                                                                                                                  • Given: A∈Rm×n

                                                                                                                                                  • Objective: decompose generic matrix A in UsVT

                                                                                                                                                    ∃U∈Rm×k,  s∈Rk:s1≥⋯≥sk≥0,  V∈Rn×ks.t.A=UsVT ∧ UTU=VTV=I

                                                                                                                                                  • Where

                                                                                                                                                    • I: identity matrix
                                                                                                                                                    • U: matrix containing eigenvectors in columns
                                                                                                                                                    • s: diagonal matrix of eigenvalues
                                                                                                                                                    U=[u1⋯un]s=[s1⋯0⋮⋱⋮0⋯sn]

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Dimensionality reduction using PCA

                                                                                                                                                  • Let: W^=[w1,...,wk] holds the first k PCs derived from centered data points X¯=[x¯1,...,x¯n]

                                                                                                                                                  • Change to reduced coordinate system with the k PCs as axis

                                                                                                                                                    T=W^TX¯∈Rk×n

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Number of principal components

                                                                                                                                                  Formula (Cumulative proportion of explained variance)

                                                                                                                                                  • Task: reduce dimensions from n to k

                                                                                                                                                  • Objective: estimate the amount of information loss

                                                                                                                                                  • Formula (FPC, ED)

                                                                                                                                                    1. Compute the cumulative variance explained by the first k eigenvalues/variances ∑j=1kλj
                                                                                                                                                    2. Normalize the cumulative variance dividing it by the sum of all the variances ∑j=1mCjj
                                                                                                                                                    ∑j=1kλj∑j=1mCjj

                                                                                                                                                  • Formula (FPC, SVD)

                                                                                                                                                    ∑j=1ksj2∑ijX¯ij2

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Clustering

                                                                                                                                                  k-means clustering

                                                                                                                                                  • Minimize the variation between each point and the centroid of the cluster
                                                                                                                                                  minC1,...,Ck∑j=1kV(Cj)
                                                                                                                                                  • Variation (squared distances)
                                                                                                                                                  V(Cj)=∑i∈Cj‖xi−μj‖2
                                                                                                                                                  • Centroid
                                                                                                                                                  μj=1|Cj|∑i∈Cjxi

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Create a graph

                                                                                                                                                  • Gaussian kernel to compute a similarity matrix
                                                                                                                                                  W(i,j)=exp⁡−|xi−xj|2σ2

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Graph terminology

                                                                                                                                                  • Degree of a node

                                                                                                                                                    di=∑jwi,j

                                                                                                                                                  • Volume of a set

                                                                                                                                                    vol(A)=∑i∈AdiA⊆V

                                                                                                                                                   

                                                                                                                                                  Normalized cut

                                                                                                                                                  • Objective: minimize

                                                                                                                                                    NCut(A,B)=Cut(A,B)V(A)+Cut(A,B)V(B)
